name: חורבת עקב
description.en: Horvat Aqav (Hirbet Mantzur al-Aqav) are archaeological remains located at the highest point of Ramat Hanadiv. The compound was used as living quarters during two main periods: the Second Temple Period and the Byzantine Period.
